claim.claim-text:
An apparatus for monitoring a hydraulic rock breaking machine (10), wherein the apparatus comprises;

at least one pressure sensing device for sensing pressure of fluid inside the rock breaking machine (10);

at least one control unit (CU) configured to receive sensed pressure data from the at least one pressure sensing device;

and wherein the control unit (CU) is configured to process the received sensing data and to provide monitoring data in accordance with a control strategy input to the control unit (CU);

characterized in that

the at least one pressure sensing device (S) is configured to sense pneumatic pressure variations inside the hydraulic rock breaking machine that are caused by reciprocating movement of a hydraulically operated percussion piston (17) of a percussion device (14) of the hydraulic rock breaking machine (10).

A hydraulic rock breaking machine (10), which is intended to be mounted to a work machine (1, 12) and comprises:
a body (16);
a percussion device (14), which is hydraulically operating and mounted inside the body (16), and is configured to generate impact pulses by means of a reciprocating piston (17) to a tool (9) mountable to a front end of the body (16); and
at least one apparatus for sensing prevailing fluid pressure inside the rock breaking machine (10);
characterized in that
the apparatus is in accordance with claims 1 - 7, whereby the hydraulic rock breaking machine (10) is provided with at least one sensor (S) for sensing pneumatic pressure inside the body (16) in order to monitor pneumatic pressure fluctuation caused by the hydraulically operated piston (17) of the hydraulic percussion device (14).

The rock breaking machine as claimed in a claim 8 or 9, characterized in that

the rock breaking machine (10) is a rock drilling machine (8) and comprises an oil mist lubrication system for providing pressurized air-oil mist flow inside the body (16);

the rock drilling machine (8) further comprises the drilling tool (9) at a front end of the body (16), or a shank adapter for connecting the drilling tool (9);

the shank adapter or the drilling tool (9) is rotated by means of a rotating device (19) via a gearing (20, 21) surrounding the shank adapter or the drilling tool (9);

the oil mist lubricating system is configured to lubricate a front space surrounding a rear end portion of the shank adapter or the drilling tool (9) and the gearing (20, 21); and

the at least one sensor is a pneumatic sensor (S) which is in pneumatic connection with the front space and is arranged to sense pneumatic pressure of the air-oil mist prevailing inside the front space.

The rock breaking machine as claimed in any one of the preceding claims 8 - 10, characterized in that

the rock breaking machine (10) is a rock drilling machine (8);

the rock drilling machine (8) comprises a rear space (26) at a rear end portion of the body (16);

the rear space (26) is limited by a rear cover (25) mounted releasably to the body (16);

the rear space (26) is in pneumatic communication with a rear end of a reciprocating piston (17) of the percussion device (14); and

the at least one sensor (S) is a pneumatic sensor (S) which is in pneumatic connection with the rear space (26) and is arranged to sense pneumatic pressure prevailing inside the rear space (26).

The rock breaking machine as claimed in any one of the preceding claims 8 - 13, characterized in that

the rock breaking machine (10) is provided with a dedicated monitoring space which is pressurized with gas and inside which a rear end (17a) of the piston (17) of the percussion device is configured to move;

and wherein at least one sensor (S) is in pneumatic connection with the dedicated monitoring space and is configured to detect fluctuating pneumatic pressure caused by the reciprocating rear end (17a) of the piston (17).

A method for monitoring operation of a hydraulic rock breaking machine (10), wherein the method comprises:
providing the rock breaking machine (10) with at least one sensing device for providing pressure data for the monitoring;
characterized by
sensing prevailing pneumatic pressure inside a body (16) of the rock breaking machine (10) by means of at least one sensing device (S);
transmitting the sensed pneumatic pressure data to at least one control unit (CU); and
processing the sensed pneumatic pressure data in the control unit (CU) and generating monitoring data.
